State files an Amended Information amending counts 1, 4, 7 and 10 to Conspiracy to Commit Burglary as PTC, contrary to Section 943.10(1m)(a) & 939.31 and 939.05 of the Wisconsin Statutes.   
Count 4 - PTC Conspiracy to Commit Burglary - No contest plea.   
Count 7 - PTC Conspiracy to Commit Burglary - No contest plea.   
Count 8 - Theft - No contest plea.   Convicted.   
State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1, 2, 3, 5, 6, 9, 10, 11, and 12 as well as uncharged incident of 15-5016, forgery from the City of Manitowoc.   Motion granted.   
Count 8 - Defendant is sentenced to nine (9) months incarceration consecutive to the sentence defendant is presently serving on 08-CF 169.   
Counts 4 and 7 - Sentences are withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for five (5) years to commence upon the completion of sentence on Count 8.  Conditions of probation are: 
1) Pay restitution as follows:   Dana Konkle $40.00; Dennis Hartlaub $1,000.00; Hastings Mutual Ins. $624.50; Linda Pekarek $1,000.00; State Farm Ins. $2,229.24; Peter Vanderkinter $500.00 and American Family Ins. $5,957.62, joint and several with anyone else prosecuted and convicted;
2) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
3) AODA assessment and follow through counseling;
4) Have no contact with the victims Dana Konkle, Dennis Hartlaub, Linda Pekarek, Richard Thomsen, Gary and Sharon Roethle and Peter Vanderkinter or their premises;
5) Maintain full-time employment or work search;
6) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
7) Have no storage or rental facility in the defendant's name or rented by another person for the defendant's use;
8) Submit DNA sample;
9) Pay costs of action; 
10) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights.  
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.   
Voter Ineligibility Notice and Acknowledgment.   
Minutes.
